race.comment: PLACID PEARL (11) big jump in class when she had the dream run along the inside to get up in a tight finish over 2000m at Randwick. Gets the same setup again and should be even stronger out to the 2400m. BESTOWER (7) consistent mare holding her form deep into the prep. Strong through the line when fifth over this trip at Rosehill. Since fitted with a 1200m tick over trial placing and any rain will help her cause. WAR RIBBON (13) form hard to fault after looming strongly at his last two runs. Gave his all with the 52kg when a gritty third over this trip at Randwick. Another who will relish a rain affected track. BELLA MONTAGNA (6) on the quick backup when she warmed up late to run fifth in easier company over this trip at Randwick. Stretches out to this trip for the first time and gets her chance. LENNOX (8) improving stayer likely to roll forward on the backup. Don't dismiss.
